excerpt: Cape Henry beachfront park & historic site with marshes, maritime forest, hiking & canoe trails.
detail_description: First Landing State Park, situated on the Cape Henry beachfront, is a historic site and natural haven boasting marshes, maritime forests, hiking trails, and canoe routes. This park is a popular destination in the Hampton Roads metro area due to its coastal location and numerous outdoor activities. It's also recognized as Virginia's first planned park and holds a place on the Register of Historic Places as Seashore State Park Historic District.
name: First Landing State Park
address: 2500 Shore Dr, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Aquarium focused on Virginia marine life, past & present, with an IMAX theater, boat tour & aviary.
detail_description: The Virginia Aquarium & Marine Science Center is a captivating destination that immerses visitors in the wonders of marine life native to Virginia, both past and present. Nestled just a mile from downtown, this attraction boasts over 300 interactive exhibits, including touch pools where you can get hands-on with stingrays and horseshoe crabs. The experience doesn't stop there; guests can marvel at an impressive array of creatures such as turtles, sharks, otters, and even Komodo dragons.
name: Virginia Aquarium & Marine Science Center
address: 717 General Booth Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Historic 18th-century lighthouse featuring tower climbs with ocean vistas, a gift shop & more.
detail_description: Nestled at the entrance of Chesapeake Bay, the Cape Henry Lighthouse is a historic gem that dates back to 1791. This iconic structure was pivotal in ensuring safe navigation for vessels entering the harbor, marking a significant milestone in maritime history. Constructed from Aquia sandstone—similar to that used in many Washington, DC buildings—the lighthouse stands as a testament to early American engineering and federal investment. Visitors can climb its tower for breathtaking ocean views and explore its charming gift shop filled with unique souvenirs.
name: Cape Henry Lighthouse
address: 583 Atlantic Ave, Fort Story, VA 23459, USA

excerpt: Vintage WWI & WWII military planes, many still in flying shape, are housed in this hangar museum.
detail_description: Nestled in the scenic Sandbridge area of Virginia Beach, the Military Aviation Museum is a treasure trove for aviation enthusiasts and history buffs alike. This impressive museum boasts one of the largest private collections of vintage military aircraft from World War I and II, many of which are still capable of flight. Visitors can explore over 100 acres filled with meticulously restored planes that played significant roles in military history, including iconic fighters and bombers.
name: Military Aviation Museum
address: 1341 Princess Anne Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23457, USA

excerpt: Pristine maritime forest & coastline not accessible by private car, with biking trails & kayaking.
detail_description: False Cape State Park, located between Back Bay and the Atlantic Ocean, offers a back-to-nature experience with its pristine maritime forest and coastline. Accessible only by hiking or boating in, the park features 15 miles of trails, untouched beaches for sunbathing and swimming, guided kayak trips, and beachfront primitive camping. Visitors can explore the historic Wash Woods community and enjoy outdoor activities such as hiking, biking through various trails, kayaking trips, beachcombing, and camping.
name: False Cape State Park
address: 4001 Sandpiper Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23456, USA

excerpt: Water slides, a tubing river & a wave pool headline this sprawling water park with 30+ rides.
detail_description: Ocean Breeze Waterpark is a vibrant oasis located just two miles south of the Oceanfront in Virginia Beach, making it an ideal destination for families seeking adventure and fun. Since its opening in 1974, this water park has become a beloved summer retreat, welcoming visitors from Memorial Day to Labor Day.
name: Ocean Breeze
address: 849 General Booth Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Regularly changing exhibitions of art such as paintings, sculptures & photography, plus classes.
detail_description: Immerse yourself in the vibrant art scene of Virginia Beach by visiting the Virginia Museum of Contemporary Art (MOCA). This museum offers a dynamic experience with its ever-changing exhibitions featuring paintings, sculptures, and photography. You can also participate in studio art classes and attend special events to deepen your understanding of contemporary art. As you explore the ViBe Creative District, take a leisurely stroll on the Mural Walking Tour to admire outdoor murals created by local artists.
name: Virginia Museum of Contemporary Art
address: 2200 Parks Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Former landfill now a city recreational area with a skate park, picnicking & sports facilities.
detail_description: Mount Trashmore Park, located in Virginia Beach, is a unique recreational area that was once a landfill but has been transformed into a vibrant community hub. Covering 165 acres, the park features two man-made mountains, two lakes, playgrounds, and a skatepark with a vert ramp. The main mountain, Mount Trashmore, stands at 60 feet tall and offers opportunities for hiking and picnicking. This eco-friendly space also includes multi-use pathways for walking and cycling.
name: Mount Trashmore Park
address: 310 Edwin Dr, Virginia Beach, VA 23462, USA

excerpt: Wetlands refuge that hosts thousands of migratory waterfowl, including snow geese & tundra swans.
detail_description: Back Bay National Wildlife Refuge is a haven for migratory waterfowl, such as snow geese and tundra swans. The refuge spans several miles of beach and marshlands, providing protection from development. Visitors can explore the area through various trails that wind through untouched coastal habitat. In addition to birdwatching, outdoor enthusiasts can enjoy hiking, biking, or leisurely strolls in the warmer months.
name: Back Bay National Wildlife Refuge
address: 4005 Sandpiper Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23456, USA

excerpt: Farm with seasonal markets & family-friendly attractions including a petting zoo & bird aviary.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Virginia Beach, Hunt Club Farm is a delightful family-owned destination that spans over thirty acres of picturesque farmland. This charming farm offers an array of seasonal attractions perfect for visitors of all ages. Kids can enjoy hands-on experiences at the Petting Farm, where they can interact with friendly animals like pigs, llamas, and goats. The BirdWalk Aviary is another highlight, featuring over 500 colorful parakeets that are sure to captivate young and old alike.
name: Hunt Club Farm
address: 2388 London Bridge Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23456, USA

excerpt: Seasonal amusement center featuring 16 rides, a go-kart track, midway games & food stands.
detail_description: Located in Virginia Beach, the Atlantic Fun Park is a seasonal amusement center that offers a wide range of attractions for visitors of all ages. From classic rides to thrilling roller coasters and go-kart tracks, this family-friendly park provides an old-school charm with a mix of modern excitement. Situated along the boardwalk near 15th Street, it features a 100-foot Ferris wheel, midway games, food stands, and various children's and family rides.
name: Atlantic Fun Park
address: 233 15th St, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Circa-1895 oceanfront cottage documenting migratory birds with paintings, artifacts & carved decoys.
detail_description: Museum dedicated to Atlantic Wildfowl, which migrate through the eastern side of the US. The museum has displays on traditional decoys, carvings life-filled with birds, and dioramas illustrating their subject. The museum is located in a heritage-packed building, the Witt Cottage, on the oceanfront of Virginia Beach.
name: Atlantic Wildfowl Heritage Museum
address: 1113 Atlantic Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Buzzing Atlantic Ocean boardwalk stretching for 3 mi., with restaurants, shops & entertainment.
detail_description: The Virginia Beach Boardwalk is a bustling 3-mile stretch along the Atlantic Ocean, offering a vibrant atmosphere with an array of restaurants, shops, and entertainment options. It provides a close-up view of the coastline without getting sandy and presents opportunities to dine at delicious eateries, shop at friendly vendors, and enjoy lively nightlife during the summer months. Visitors can capture memorable moments while indulging in local cuisine or engaging in activities like biking or rollerblading along the boardwalk.
name: Virginia Beach Oceanfront Boardwalk
address: Virginia Beach Boardwalk, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Quiet seaside enclave south of Virginia Beach featuring a sandy shoreline, vacation houses & condos.
detail_description: Sandbridge Beach is a serene coastal retreat located just 15 miles south of the bustling Virginia Beach. This 5-mile stretch of sandy shoreline offers a peaceful alternative to the more touristy areas, making it perfect for swimmers, surfers, and families seeking a quieter beach experience. The proximity to vacation rentals and the nearby Back Bay National Wildlife Refuge and False Cape State Park add to its allure.
name: Sandbridge Beach
address: Virginia Beach, VA, USA

excerpt: Fully accessible beach park featuring a playground, raised sand tables, a sensory board & more.
detail_description: Grommet Island Park, located in Virginia Beach, is a unique and fully accessible beach park designed to cater to individuals of all abilities. Spanning approximately 15,000 square feet, the park features a variety of inclusive amenities such as a sway boat, raised sand tables for building sandcastles at an accessible height, and a sensory board tailored for visually impaired and autistic children.
name: Grommet Island Park
address: Boardwalk &, 2nd St, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Costumed guides in this plantation owner's home detail the Tidewater lifestyle of the 18th century.
detail_description: The Lynnhaven House, built around 1725, offers a fascinating look into the Tidewater lifestyle of the 18th century. This well-preserved example of early Virginia vernacular architecture provides insight into the lives of its original builder, Francis Thelaball, his family, and the enslaved individuals who worked on the plantation. Visitors can explore unique architectural features such as brick archways, a closed-spindle staircase, and ships lap floor construction.
name: Lynnhaven House
address: 4409 Wishart Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23455, USA

excerpt: Virginia Beach, a coastal city in southeastern Virginia, lies where the Chesapeake Bay meets the Atlantic Ocean. A 3-mile boardwalk stretches along its beach-lined oceanfront. The bayside First Landing State Park marks the 1607 arrival of the Jamestown colonists from England. The Virginia Aquarium & Marine Science Center exhibits ocean life including sharks, rays and sea turtles in globally themed habitats.
detail_description: Virginia Beach is a coastal city in southeastern Virginia, where the Chesapeake Bay meets the Atlantic Ocean. The 3-mile boardwalk along its beach-lined oceanfront and First Landing State Park, marking the arrival of Jamestown colonists, are popular attractions. The Virginia Aquarium & Marine Science Center showcases ocean life in themed habitats. The Hampton Roads metro area offers outdoor activities and historic sites, including campgrounds and RV parks near Virginia Beach at First Landing State Park.
name: Virginia Beach
address: Virginia, USA

excerpt: White clapboard museum devoted to coastal rescue missions & shipwrecks plus a nautical gift shop.
detail_description: The Virginia Beach Surf & Rescue Museum is a charming white clapboard establishment that pays homage to the area's maritime heritage and the brave surf rescue teams who have safeguarded its shores. Nestled within the historic DeWitt Cottage, this museum delves into the evolution of beach safety, highlighting the vital contributions of lifeguards and shipwreck rescuers throughout history.
name: Virginia Beach Surf & Rescue Museum
address: 2401 Atlantic Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Museum in a historic 1830 brick manor house beside the river, plus paranormal tours.
detail_description: The Ferry Plantation House, located in Virginia Beach, is a historic 1830 brick manor house with a rich history dating back to 1642. It was named after the ferry boat service that operated on the Lynnhaven waterway. The current house was rebuilt using bricks from the original manor house that burned down in 1828.
name: Ferry Plantation House
address: 4136 Cheswick Ln, Virginia Beach, VA 23455, USA

detail_description: In the ViBe Creative District, located at the Virginia Beach Oceanfront, there's a charming coffee shop situated at 1682 Baltic Ave. The establishment welcomes visitors daily from 7 AM to 3 PM, offering an array of delightful beverages to satisfy your cravings.
name: ViBe Creative District
address: Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Lined with hotels & eateries, this expansive walkway hosts numerous summer events & concerts.
detail_description: The Virginia Beach Boardwalk is a bustling three-mile walkway lined with hotels, restaurants, and shops. It's a hub for summer events and concerts, offering visitors an up-close view of the coastline without getting sandy. The boardwalk is perfect for strolling, rollerblading, or biking while enjoying the local cuisine and friendly vendors. This iconic spot features the famous Neptune Statue and is a popular destination for tourists seeking fun in the sun during Virginia Beach's summer months.
name: Virginia Beach Boardwalk
address: Virginia Beach, VA, USA

excerpt: April azaleas are the showstoppers at this lush green space, which also features 450 rose varieties.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Norfolk, Virginia, the Norfolk Botanical Garden spans an impressive 155 acres and is a true paradise for nature enthusiasts. This vibrant garden showcases over forty themed areas, each offering its own unique charm. In April, visitors are treated to stunning displays of azaleas that steal the spotlight alongside an extensive collection of 450 rose varieties. Among its many attractions, you'll find a serene Japanese Garden designed in traditional style with hills and ponds that invite tranquility.
name: Norfolk Botanical Garden
address: 6700 Azalea Garden Rd, Norfolk, VA 23518, USA

excerpt: Tours of this circa 1719 cottage, one of the state's oldest, offer a glimpse into colonial life.
detail_description: The Thoroughgood House, dating back to 1719, is one of the oldest cottages in the state and offers tours providing insight into colonial life. It is part of the City of Virginia Beach History Museums, which also includes the Francis Land House, Lynnhaven House, and Princess Anne County Training School/Union Kempsville High School Museum.
name: The Thoroughgood House
address: 1636 Parish Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23455, USA

detail_description: Located on the Virginia Beach resort strip, Nightmare Mansion is a renowned haunted house that has been terrifying visitors for over three decades. Considered one of America's most frightening haunted houses, it offers a spine-chilling experience for thrill-seekers and ghost enthusiasts. With realistic props, sound effects, and trained actors creating ghoulish scenes, this attraction provides an adrenaline rush that is not for the faint-hearted. The narrow hallways of the mansion were once home to Dr.
name: Nightmare Mansion
address: 2008 Atlantic Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Veteran 17.6-mi. bridge-tunnel & "engineering wonder" crossing at the mouth of the Chesapeake Bay.
detail_description: The Chesapeake Bay Bridge-Tunnel is a remarkable 17.6-mile bridge-tunnel system that serves as an engineering marvel at the mouth of the Chesapeake Bay. It provides a seamless connection between Virginia's Eastern Shore and the mainland, offering travelers a scenic and convenient way to cross the bay. Completed in 1964, this iconic structure was designed to eliminate the reliance on ferries for transporting passengers and cargo, making it an essential part of Virginia's transportation network.
name: Chesapeake Bay Bridge-Tunnel
address: Virginia, USA

detail_description: Sandbridge Beach, located near the Virginia Beach Boardwalk, offers a quieter alternative to the bustling main attractions. Spanning five miles, this serene beach boasts stunning dunes, pristine coastline, and captivating wildlife. Away from the energetic resort area, it provides a peaceful and relaxed atmosphere for visitors seeking a tranquil retreat. It's an ideal spot for leisurely walks, beach picnics, and quiet relaxation amidst breathtaking natural landscapes.
name: Sandbridge Beach
address: Virginia Beach, VA 23456, USA

excerpt: Venerable wood fishing pier, open seasonally, with a tackle shop, seafood restaurant & rod rentals.
detail_description: The Virginia Beach Fishing Pier is a beloved seasonal wooden pier offering a tackle shop, seafood restaurant, and rod rentals. It's a family-friendly spot where you can spend an afternoon trying your luck at catching roundheads, trout, whiting, Spanish mackerel, and blue crab. Whether you're an experienced angler or just starting out, the pier welcomes all to enjoy fishing and crabbing without needing a license or equipment.
name: Virginia Beach Fishing Pier
address: 1413 Atlantic Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

detail_description: Edgar Cayce's A.R.E. Association for Research and Enlightenment is a hub of metaphysical research inspired by the life and work of Edgar Cayce, a prominent figure in the early 20th century known for his healing and psychic abilities. Established in 1931 at his estate in Virginia Beach, the A.R.E. aims to scientifically explore paranormal phenomena, extra-sensory perception, and holistic healing.
name: Edgar Cayce's A.R.E. Association for Research and Enlightenment
address: 215 67th Street at, 6798 Atlantic Ave #6700, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Statue commemorating the 19th-century wreck of a Norwegian ship & the local rescue efforts.
detail_description: The Norwegian Lady is a significant statue in Virginia Beach, commemorating the tragic wreck of the Norwegian bark Dictator in 1891. The original wooden figurehead from the ship stood as a memorial for 60 years before being replaced by a nine-foot bronze replica commissioned by the city of Moss, Norway and presented to Virginia Beach in 1962. This gesture united the two sister cities, with an exact duplicate erected in Moss.
name: Norwegian Lady
address: 2500 Atlantic Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Charming cottage restaurant serving New American breakfast & lunch dishes featuring local produce.
detail_description: The Bee and The Biscuit is a charming Virginia Beach restaurant located in a 1919 cottage in the Pungo district. Opened by Karen Johnson in 2016, this delightful eatery offers a farm-to-table dining experience with locally-sourced ingredients.
name: The Bee and The Biscuit
address: 1785 Princess Anne Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23456, USA

excerpt: Boasting a 3-mile boardwalk, this bustling area offers sandy beaches, cafes & shops.
detail_description: Virginia Beach Oceanfront is a bustling area with a 3-mile boardwalk, sandy beaches, cafes, and shops. It offers year-round activities such as the Cherry Blossom Festival in spring and extended summer weather leading into fall. With 35 miles of oceanfront beaches, most of the action happens in the resort area where visitors can enjoy sunbathing and beach-front activities.
name: Virginia Beach Oceanfront
address: 1700 Atlantic Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

detail_description: The Neptune Festival, held annually in late September, is a vibrant event that has been a staple for 46 years. The festival boasts daily concerts, an extensive arts and crafts show, and the renowned International Sandsculpting Championship. Additionally, Virginia Beach hosts other engaging events such as the Craft Beer Festival featuring live music and specialty brews, the Cupcake Festival with live music performances, and charity walks like the JT Walk for ALS culminating in a lively beach celebration.
name: Neptune Festival
address: 265 Kings Grant Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23452, USA

detail_description: Virginia Beach is a haven for beer enthusiasts, offering a variety of breweries to explore. Back Bay Brewing Co. and Commonwealth Brewing Company are popular choices, each with its own unique atmosphere and selection of beers. Smartmouth Pilot House, located just blocks from the Oceanfront, offers a dog-friendly outdoor drinking space in a former post office. Tarnished Truth Distilling Company stands out as the first in-hotel distillery in the United States, situated within The Historic Cavalier Hotel & Beach Club.
name: Tarnished Truth Distilling Co.
address: 4200 Atlantic Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Small park with 9 bronze statues depicting early local naval history, WWII & the modern day.
detail_description: Located at 25th & Atlantic avenues in Virginia Beach, Naval Aviation Monument Park is a small but significant park featuring nine bronze statues that depict the early local naval history, World War II, and modern-day naval aviation. The monument pays tribute to the Marine Corps and Coast Guard as well. It serves as an outdoor art park and offers a glimpse into the history of aircraft, ships, and the people who dedicated their lives to national defense.
name: Naval Aviation Monument Park
address: 25th Street &, 2500 Atlantic Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: This grassy beachfront park with frequent live music has large statue of the Roman god Neptune.
detail_description: Neptune's Park is a charming beachfront park located in the heart of Virginia Beach Oceanfront. It features a large statue of the Roman god Neptune and offers frequent live music, making it a popular spot for outdoor events. The park also includes shops, restaurants, a playground, an oceanfront stage, and a Splash Pad. Visitors can enjoy picturesque views of the surroundings and explore nearby amenities such as star hotels, nightclubs, bars, and boutiques.
name: Neptune's Park
address: 3001 Atlantic Ave, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Forest attraction featuring several treetop trails of varying difficulty with climbing & zip-lining.
detail_description: Nestled within the Virginia Aquarium, The Adventure Park at Virginia Aquarium is an exhilarating forest attraction that combines the thrill of a theme park with the beauty of nature. With 17 unique Nature Paths and over 30 zipline rides, visitors can explore treetop trails of varying difficulty levels, reaching heights above the ground floor. This expansive obstacle course features swinging stairs and challenging aerial walks securely roped into the trees, providing an adrenaline-boosting experience for all ages.
name: The Adventure Park at Virginia Aquarium
address: 801 General Booth Blvd, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Beach park on 130+ acres with swimming, fishing & crabbing plus picnic shelters & sports courts.
detail_description: Little Island Park, located in Sandbridge near Back Bay National Wildlife Refuge, offers over 130 acres of outdoor fun. The park features a 400-foot fishing pier and a pristine beach for swimming, fishing, and beachcombing. Visitors can also enjoy picnic shelters and sports courts throughout the park. Additionally, it's a great spot for kids to play near the pier or rent fat-tire bikes from Surf and Adventure Co. to ride on the sand.
name: Little Island Park
address: 3820 Sandpiper Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23456, USA

excerpt: 42-acre parkland on the lake, offering shady hiking trails, a playground, docks & fishing spots.
detail_description: Lake Smith Lake Lawson Natural Area, located in the Bayside neighborhood of Virginia Beach, is a 42-acre parkland offering a variety of outdoor activities. With shady hiking trails, a playground, fishing spots, and docks for canoeing and kayaking, it's considered one of the best natural destinations in Virginia Beach. The area features diverse habitats and wildlife to observe while enjoying a peaceful hike around the lakes. Visitors appreciate its proximity to Virginia Beach and its tranquil atmosphere with convenient parking.
name: Lake Smith Lake Lawson Natural Area
address: 5381 Shell Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23455, USA

excerpt: While go carts are the main attraction here, there's also paintball, small rides & mini-golf.
detail_description: Motor World in Virginia Beach is a thrilling destination for racing enthusiasts and families alike. With over a dozen go-kart styles and tracks, including the Adult Speed Track, it's the ultimate place to satisfy your need for speed. The park also features paintball fields, miniature golf, bumper boats, the Skycoaster, and more. Young motorsport fans can enjoy the outdoor go-karting arena with 250+ obstacle courses and other exciting rides like Gravity Storm.
name: Motor World
address: 700 S Birdneck Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23451, USA

excerpt: Outdoor amphitheater with 20,000 seats hosting summer music festivals & national big-name bands.
detail_description: The Veterans United Home Loans Amphitheater at Virginia Beach is a popular outdoor venue with a seating capacity of over 20,000, making it an ideal spot for summer music festivals and big-name band performances. From national headliners to local favorites, the amphitheater offers a diverse lineup of musical acts. Guests can enjoy up-close experiences near the stage or opt for a more relaxed setting on the spacious lawn with lawn chairs and picnic blankets.
name: Veterans United Home Loans Amphitheater at Virginia Beach
address: 3550 Cellar Door Way, Virginia Beach, VA 23456, USA

excerpt: Sprawling park with 700+ animals from 150+ species, plus tours, gardens & kids' camps.
detail_description: The Virginia Zoo, located on the shores of the Lafayette River, is a sprawling park that houses over 700 animals from more than 150 species. Visitors can explore exhibits like the World of Reptiles and the Trail of the Tiger, where they can see red pandas, siamangs, and Malayan tigers. The zoo's staff are dedicated to preserving global and local biodiversity through various initiatives aimed at protecting vulnerable species.
name: Virginia Zoo
address: 3500 Granby St, Norfolk, VA 23504, USA

excerpt: Huge multi-sport & multi-surface spot for sporting events from high school to professional levels.
detail_description: The Virginia Beach Sportsplex is a vast facility that accommodates various sports on different terrains, catering to both high school and professional levels. It boasts football fields, tennis courts, track and field amenities, as well as the esteemed Field Hockey Regional Training Center. With a seating capacity of 6,000, the Sportsplex Stadium provides an impressive venue for sporting events. Additionally, there is a pleasant indoor arena where patrons can enjoy beverages like Bud Light and Mic Ultra.
name: Virginia Beach Sportsplex
address: 2044 Landstown Centre Wy, Virginia Beach, VA 23456, USA

excerpt: Exhibits detailing the region's first school for African-American children, with artifacts & photos.
detail_description: The Princess Anne County Training School/Union Kempsville High School Museum in Virginia Beach offers a unique look into the history of the region's first school for African-American children. Originally established in 1930 and later renamed Union Kempsville High School, this museum showcases the legacy of the African American community's efforts to provide education for their children.
name: Princess Anne County Training School/Union Kempsville High School Museum
address: 5100 Cleveland St, Virginia Beach, VA 23462, USA

excerpt: Sandbridge, in the U.S. state of Virginia, is a coastal community of Virginia Beach, located along the coastline on the Currituck Banks Peninsula at the northern end of the Outer Banks. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Sandbridge is a serene coastal community situated in Virginia Beach, Virginia. Nestled along the Currituck Banks Peninsula at the northern end of the Outer Banks, this beach offers a tranquil escape from the bustling city. It is located in front of a residential area, providing visitors with a peaceful and relaxing environment to enjoy the natural beauty of its coastline.
name: Sandbridge
address: Virginia Beach, VA, USA

excerpt: Down-to-earth restaurant with coastal decor for seafood dishes, local beers & signature cocktails.
detail_description: Blue Seafood & Spirits is a chef-owned restaurant located on Upton Drive in Virginia Beach, offering a casual yet elegant dining experience with coastal decor. The 60-seater eatery is known for its high-quality, fresh seafood dishes such as tempura fried shrimp and crab cakes. Chef Charles Thain's dedication to serving delicious meals has earned the restaurant a reputation as one of the best spots in VA Beach for seafood.
name: Blue Seafood & Spirits
address: 2181 Upton Dr #420, Virginia Beach, VA 23454, USA

detail_description: Chesapeake Beach, also known as Chics or Chicks Beach, is a serene and picturesque destination nestled along the shores of Virginia Beach. The beach is renowned for its breathtaking sunsets over the Chesapeake Bay, making it a favorite spot for locals and tourists alike.
name: Chesapeake Beach
address: Virginia Beach, VA, USA

excerpt: Popular sandy beach with seasonal lifeguards & 2 surfing areas offering lessons.
detail_description: Croatan Beach in Virginia is a hidden gem just south of the resort strip, offering a quieter and more laid-back atmosphere compared to the bustling resort area. This mile-long sandy beach features two designated surfing areas where surfers can test their skills and take lessons. The neighborhood of Croatan is known for its stunning waterfront homes, walkable streets, and easy access to downtown. It's popular with families and singles alike due to its relaxed vibe.

address: Virginia Beach, VA, USA

detail_description: The Bagel Baker is a classic New York-style bagel shop that offers fresh, delicious bagels at reasonable prices. The shop is family-owned and operated and is perfect for breakfast or any time of day.
name: The Bagel Baker
address: 1340 N Great Neck Rd #1248, Virginia Beach, VA 23454, USA

excerpt: Year-round site hosting a butcher shop, bakery, seafood market & restaurant, with events & programs.
detail_description: Virginia Beach Farmers Market is a year-round destination featuring a variety of offerings such as a butcher shop, bakery, seafood market, and restaurant. The ViBe Creative District in the area serves as a vibrant hub for various creative outlets and hosts events like art festivals and walking tours. Visitors can also explore the Virginia Museum of Contemporary Art to learn about contemporary art through changing exhibits and special events.
name: Virginia Beach Farmers Market
address: 3640 Dam Neck Rd, Virginia Beach, VA 23453, USA

detail_description: Oceanfront is a vibrant resort area with a lively atmosphere, featuring an array of large hotels, restaurants, shops, and entertainment options. The 59-block-long Boardwalk offers well-maintained landscaping, bike paths, parks, and live entertainment during the summer. Recently restored to its former glory, Oceanfront boasts luxurious accommodations with spacious rooms and suites, a spa, distillery, private beach club, and fine dining options.
